<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE reference  PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Reference//EN" "reference.dtd">
<reference id="lcCorrectResponse2" xml:lang="en-us" rev="DITA1.3">
  <title><xmlelement>lcCorrectResponse2</xmlelement></title>
  <shortdesc>The <xmlelement>lcCorrectResponse2</xmlelement> element in an assessment interaction
    indicates a correct response. This element replaces the
    <xmlelement>lcCorrectResponse</xmlelement> element in DITA 1.2.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>lcCorrectResponse2</indexterm>
        <indexterm>learning and training
          elements<indexterm>lcCorrectResponse2</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <section>
      <p>In a <xmlelement>lcHotspot2</xmlelement> interaction, indicate the correct hotspot by
        setting the <xmlatt>value</xmlatt> attribute of <xmlelement>lcCorrectResponse2</xmlelement> to the id of the
        "correct" area in the image map.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="contains"
      conref="../../common/commonNavLibraryTable.dita#contentmodel-lcCorrectResponse2/contains"
      otherprops="contains"></section>
    


    <section id="inheritance" otherprops="inheritance">
      <title>Inheritance</title>
      <p>+ topic/data learningInteractionBase2-d/data learning2-d/lcCorrectResponse2 </p>
    </section>
    <example conref="lcTrueFalse2.dita#lcTrueFalse2/example" id="example"/>
    <example id="example-with-lcHotSpot">
      <title>Example with the <xmlelement>lcHotspot2</xmlelement> element</title>
      <codeblock conref="lcHotspot2.dita#lcHotspot2/example-lchotspot"/>
    </example>
    <section id="attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <p>The following attributes are available on this element: <xref
          href="../attributes/universalAttributes.dita"/>, <xref
          href="../attributes/commonAttributes.dita#common-atts/outputclass"/>, and the attributes
        defined below.</p>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><xmlatt>name</xmlatt></dt>
          <dd>The name used to indicate this data. The default value for this attribute is
            "lcCorrectResponse2".</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><xmlatt>value</xmlatt>
            <ph conref="../../common/conref-attribute.dita#conref-attribute/required-attr"/></dt>
          <dd>The value. In an <xmlelement>lcHotspot2</xmlelement> interaction, set the value to the
            id corresponding to the correct area in the imagemap.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
      
    </section>
  </refbody>
</reference>
